# --- snap / grid / highlight key actions (doc/claude/specs/keybind_snap_grid_actions.md) --
# These ship UNBOUND: no built-in default chord. Each is a registered action, also
# reachable from the menus (Options / View). Map any action to any chord with
#   xschem bind key <keysym> <mods> canvas <action>
# Keysyms: g=103  G=71  %=37  s=115  (run `xev` for others); mods 0|ctrl|alt|shift|super.
# GOTCHA: Shift changes the produced keysym (Shift-g -> 'G'/71), same as Ctrl-Shift-2
# above -- the examples use the actual produced keysyms.

# CTRL-G toggles grid visibility (active):
xschem bind key 103 ctrl canvas view.toggle_draw_grid

# CTRL+Plus / CTRL+Minus : grow / shrink the DISPLAYED text size of selected text notes
# and pin/net-label names (~10%, min step, per-type floor). Other objects ignored.
# Four keysyms cover both the main row and the numeric keypad; the C key path strips
# Shift for printable keys, so Ctrl+Shift+= (main-row '+') arrives as keysym 43 (plus)
# with mods=ctrl. 43=plus  45=minus  65451=KP_Add  65453=KP_Subtract. Rebind freely.
# See doc/claude/specs/text_size_scroll.md.
xschem bind key 43    ctrl canvas edit.text_grow      ;# Ctrl+Shift+=  (main-row +)
xschem bind key 65451 ctrl canvas edit.text_grow      ;# Ctrl+KP_Add  (keypad +)
xschem bind key 45    ctrl canvas edit.text_shrink    ;# Ctrl+-       (main-row -)
xschem bind key 65453 ctrl canvas edit.text_shrink    ;# Ctrl+KP_Subtract (keypad -)

